  "response": "Yes, money laundering is illegal in virtually every country around the world. It involves the process of making illegally obtained money (often from activities like drug trafficking, fraud, or corruption) appear legitimate by passing it through a complex sequence of banking transfers or commercial transactions. The purpose is to obscure the original source of the funds.\n\nGovernments and international organizations have established strict laws and regulations to combat money laundering because it facilitates criminal activities, undermines financial systems, and can harm economies. Penalties for money laundering can be severe, including hefty fines, asset forfeiture, and imprisonment.\n\nIf you have specific questions or concerns, it's always best to consult a legal professional for advice.",
